Title: Openers
WorkoutDescription: Openers...loosen the legs and get them ready to fire! Ride between 90-100 rpm. . 10' WU . 2 x (1' @ perceived race pace + 4' Recovery)

Title: 2400: 2x(2x200 tempo + 100 Pull + 300 paddles)
WorkoutDescription: One key to successful open water swimming is training for variable intensities that you will experience throughout the race. In this workout really focus on the specified increased pace on the sets of 200’s. Can you swim faster on the 2nd round of 200s? . 6 x 100 Free :15 12 x 50 (odds catch-up drill/evens pull) :15 . Main Set: 2 x 200 (1st 100 hard/2nd 100 relaxed) :30 100 Pull Easy :15 300 Pull with Paddles 1:00 . 2 x 200 (1st 100 relaxed/2nd 100 fast) :30 100 Pull Easy :15 300 Pull with Paddles 1:00 . 100 CD

Title: 30': Gradually build 10' to shakeout body
WorkoutDescription: Start of easy and then after 15', slightly build the pace over the next 10'. Don't overtax your body, just get the HR up a little. Shut it down for the last 5'

Title: 2700yds: broken 1650 + 12x50
WorkoutDescription: Today we're going to have only a few quick sets. Everything else is easy and focus on your form! . Broken 1650 with lots of different stuff..details are below: 400 Pull :45 300 (50 swim + 25 OWS, repeat) :45 100 Smooth to setup fast swim :20 300 STRONG (I want a time) :20 100 easy :30 3 x 150 :20 1. 100 Free + 50 choice 2. 25 drill, 25 kick, 25 swim, repeat 3. Build each 50 . 400 Pull breathe every 3 1:00 . 12 x 50 :10 1. Drill (mix them up) 2. Kick + Swim 3. Build 4. Easy & Smooth Repeat.... . 150 CD

Title: 45': Mixed - with medicine ball squats, leg raises & swiss ball bridges
WorkoutDescription: Warm-up: 5-10' on elliptical, spin bike, easy jog, rowing machine, or jumping rope...get the blood moving . Repeat this circuit 3 times... 10 x push-ups 1' plank 10 x swiss ball bridges 5 x chin-ups (or as many as you can do up to 5) 1' rest . 3 x 12 reps lat pull down (light weight) 3 x 12 reps shoulder raises (light weight) 3 x 12 reps bicep curls (light weight)  3 x 10 reps medicine ball overhead squat (light weight) 3 x 10 reps medicine ball leg raises 1' plank .
CoachComments: Swiss Ball Bridge (video) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QWlEW8PA4iw Medicine Ball Overhead Squat (video) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F70iX803-CM Medicine Ball Leg Raises (video) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4zWYlhOYvMM

Title: Bike - FTP Power Test
WorkoutDescription: FTP Power Test . 20' progressive WU, smoothly and gradually increasing power from easy to near time-trial effort . 3 x (1' hard effort (think short hill climb or Sprint distance Tri Race Pace) + 2' easy spin recovery) . 3' hard effort (think 3' hill climb or Olympic Distance Tri Race Pace) . 3' VERY easy recovery . 20' time trial @ highest sustainable power* . 5' easy CD spin
CoachComments: *NOTE: Avoid starting out too hard!! Effort should increase throughout while power remains steady, in an ideal test. As you're nearing the end of the 20', try to tap into your reserves, giving it all you have in the final minute of the TT effort. Wear your HRM for this test as well. Be sure to give me all relevant data, uploading your file(s) into TP. Your FTP will be defined as 95% of the average power you achieve during the 20' test.

WorkoutDescription: Easy transition run if you have time.
Unstructured run on rolling terrain. Pace is up to you. Find a trail if you want. Enjoy yourself! Extend up to an hour. Be ready for the larger workout the following day.

Outdoor or Indoor bike. Workout is up to you. Looking for base building training session with a few punchy (e.g. hills) efforts. Your goal is to have fun and keep the HR/Power down except when you decide to go. Extend up to 3 hours.

Title: 40': 6 punchy 90" incline repeats
WorkoutDescription: Short, punchy efforts on a good incline that is less than 1/4 mile. If on a tready, make the efforts around 60-90 seconds in duration at 4-5% incline. . 10-15' WU . Repeat this cycle and beat the pace or time for each intensity level on the 2nd round. Feel free to take 30-60 seconds rest in between each effort 60-90" hill @ moderate pace + 2-3' recovery 60-90" hill @ faster pace + 2-3' recovery 60-90" hill @ fastest pace + 2-3' recovery . 5-10' CD

Title: 2700yds: Beat previous distance split
WorkoutDescription: The main set is an interesting one. Your goal is to swim smooth and easy except for the last 100. Directions are below but keep in mind that your total time for each swim including :10 rest should beat the previous swim’s split for that distance. For example, your total time for the 200 is 3:00. This should beat the 200 split of the 300 you swam. Good luck! . WU 300 Choice . 3x100’s, 4x75’s, 4x50’s :10 100s: Breathe on weak side on odd lengths 75s: Middle 25 Fist drill 50s: Build . Take 10 seconds rest before the last 100 of each distance. The last 100 is FAST. Everything else is easy/moderate pace.  500 1:00 400 1:00 300 1:00 200 1:00 100 1:00 . 100 CD

Title: 90': Aerobic Punch - 3 x (15' High AeT + 1' LT + 1' AeC + 3' easy)
WorkoutDescription: Aerobic Punch. Ride is available on TrainerRoad under team workouts. If outside, right at an aerobic/base pace with 7-10 short efforts that are uncomfortable. If inside, this is to build your aerobic engine while simulating short, punchy climbs . Repeat this set 4 times....gradually build first high AeT set to use as warm-up 15' High AeT @ 90-100 rpm 1' LT @ 85-90 rpm 1' AeC @ 80-85 rpm 3' easy @ 95+ rpm . 10' CD

Title: 2500yds: 600 + 200 Fun
WorkoutDescription: Use the 600s as warm-up/active recovery, chance to focus on form, and strength building during the pull sets. You don't have to go fast there. The 200 is your speed area. . 600 WU 1:00 200 @ comfortable pace :30 . 600 (50 Drill + 50 Free, repeat) 1:00 200 faster than previous :30 . 600 (Pull Buoy w paddles if you have 'em) 1:00 200 fastest of the day! :30 . 100 CD

Title: 60': 2x8' Cruise Intervals + 2x8' Spicy Cruise Intervals
WorkoutDescription: Everyone loves a good cruise interval session...this one we're adding some spice at the end . 10' progressive WU . 5' tempo + 5' easy . 2 x (8' tempo + 2' easy) . 2 x (4' tempo + 2' LT + 1' AeC + 3' easy)

Title: 3000yds: 3x(4x25 drill + 2x100 smooth + 400 pull)
WorkoutDescription: Treat today as an "easier" day where you focusing on your stroke put still logging some distance. Take the drills slow and and really "feel" the water! . 4 x 200 (odd: free, even: pull) :30 . Really think about your high elbow and catch 4 x 25 (odd: right arm only, even: left arm only) :15 2 x 100 smooth and easy :15 400 Pull (use either a buoy or paddles) 1:00 . 4 x 25 (odd: FTD, even: fist only) :15 2 x 100 smooth and easy :15 400 Pull (use either a buoy or paddles) 1:00 . Do it again...really drive home the importance of that catch and high elbow! 4 x 25 (odd: right arm only, even: left arm only) :15 2 x 100 smooth and easy :15 400 Pull (use either a buoy or paddles) 1:00 . 100 CD
Mountain Bike ride in the snow

Title: 65': Netflix and Chill - base miles with some tempo
WorkoutDescription: Just in case you can't run outside or you're an overachiever, here's another workout for the snow. The idea here is to relax, turn on something enjoyable and knock out some miles. Watch the changes in cadence! . 5' WU @ 100 rpm . Three times through this main set 10' High AeT @ 95 rpm 5' tempo @ 95 rpm 5' easy @ 100 rpm
Go run in the snow if you can! Extend up to 1 hour if you are warm enough. Forget about pace and just have fun. Keep the strides short and expect this to be work!

Title: 120': Two long mountains + Two cruise intervals
WorkoutDescription: Two mountain climbs and some cruise intervals. No joke workout that is available in TrainerRoad. In case devices are not working, use relative perceived exertion (RPE) as follows: tempo=7 out of 10, LT=8 out of 10, AeC=9 out of 10. . 20' WU @ 95 rpm. Build to low tempo . Run though this set 2 times. Imagine climbing a large hill...ok mountain and then flying down the backside of it....go REALLY easy on the intensity but please keep the cadence high. Feel free to go into aerobic tuck too! 10' tempo @ 65-75 rpm 5' LT @ 65-75 rpm 2' AeC @ 65-75 rpm 8' easy @ 100 rpm . 15' AeT @ 90-100 rpm . Cruise intervals...do the first one at low tempo and the second & third ones, wherever you feel like you can hang based the strength of your legs after the 2 mountains. 2 x (10' tempo @ 90-100 rpm + 5' easy) . 5' CD

Title: 35': Recovery run with 2-3' 10k burst
WorkoutDescription: Run on rolling terrain or keep the tready at 1-2%. Start the run off easy and keep the cadence high. After 20-25', give me one nice, long burst (2-3') @ perceived 10k pace. Don't let your form suffer. Then drop it back to an easy pace. If you're tired, only do 20-25' in total duration. If you feel good, do 30-40'.

Title: 60': Recovery w hot WU & 30" LTs
WorkoutDescription: Workout is available on TrainerRoad (Recovery w hot WU & 30" LTs). Long warm-up with high cadence and short efforts to shake the legs out. Then some more short sessions with heat but always done using high cadence (neuromuscular system) and not your big muscle groups. Make sure you start the efforts at the end on the lower end. Your legs should feel better as the workout goes on. If not, please let me know! If outside, take a long warm-up and do short spin-ups with intensity. . 10’ Easy WU . 4’ AeT + 1’ high AeT @ 100 rpm 4’ AeT + 1’ low tempo @ 100 rpm 4’ AeT + 1’ tempo @ 100 rpm . 10’ AeT @ 90-100 rpm . 6 x (30” LT @ 100 rpm + 2’ easy) . 10’ CD
Recovery run to and from high school

Title: 2600yds: 2x[(4x75) + (4x100 pull)] + 6x25 hypox
WorkoutDescription: Active Recovery day. Your focus is to have fun in the pool . WU-600 (100 swim, 50 choice, repeat) 4 x 75 (free+non-free+free) :15 4 x 100 (25 Finter tip drag + 75 Free):15 . 4 x 75 (25 Build + 50 easyl) :15 4 x 100 pull (25 Catch-up + 75 Free). Use buoy, paddles, or snorkel :15 . 6 x 50 (2 Build + 1 easy; repeat) :20 6 x 25 :15  #1 = Only take 3 breaths  #2 = Only take 2 breaths  #3 = Only take 1 breath  Second time around, can you take 1 less per 25???? . 150 CD

500 Free WU 400 IM Drill 4 x 50 Golf *Golf today = Swim a 50 and add your number of strokes with the time in seconds. Try different stroke rates to achieve the lowest total number, which will determine your most efficient stroke. Remember the pace and “feel” for the number of strokes. 5 x 100 @ Golf Score :15 100 Easy 5 x 100 @ Golf Score :10 500 Pull 200 CD

Shorter run but your goal is to increase the pace or intensity slightly every 5 minutes. My recommendation is to start around marathon perceived exertion and then keep dialing it up. Shut it down with 2-3' to go so you get a little CD mixed in at the end. Extend up to 40' if you're feeling it.

Title: 2600yds: 3x(3x100 pace) + 3x50 few breaths as possible
WorkoutDescription: The 100s are challenging because the first one you do, sets the tone and, like all things, I want you to descend it (get faster as you go!). The last part is just for fun and to challenge your tired muscles & body. . 300 (75 Free + 25 Choice) :30 200 (25 Drill + 75 Free) :30 100 Smooth Free :30 . 4 x 50 Build :30 . Repeat this set 3 times through…try to drop 1 second from your first 100 at the beginning of the 2nd and 3rd set so you get faster for all 3 x 100s. Take 15 seconds rest after each 100. Try to hit those target times! . 3 x 100s (Pace, Strong, Easy)   1. Comfortable pace capture your time  2. Drop 5 seconds from #1  3. Add 5 seconds to #1 200 Pull Easy…active recovery :30 . 3 x 50 Free :30 (Take as few breaths as possible! Start by taking 2 on first 25 and 3 on last 25. Next time you go, decrease it. I found my rhythm by taking 1 breath on the first 25 and 2 on the 2nd 25. What's yours?) . 150 CD

Progression run. Looking for you to decrease your mile time by 15-30 seconds each time so make sure you don't go out too fast! . 1 mile warm-up 1 mile @ half marathon or marathon pace 1 mile 15-30 seconds faster 1 mile 15-30 seconds quicker CD with remaining time

Title: 60': AeT/High AeT @ mixed cadences
WorkoutDescription: Steady aerobic riding with mixed cadence to use different muscle groups and shake the legs out. . 15' AeT @ 95+ RPM . 10' AeT + 5' High AeT @ 85-90 RPM . 10' AeT + 5' High AeT @ 100 RPM . 10' High AeT @ 85-90 RPM . 5' CD

Title: 45': 4 x (3-4' tempo aka half marathon RPE)
WorkoutDescription: After a 5' WU, find some hills and knock out 4 x (3-4' tempo efforts). If you can't find a climb, set the tready to 3% and start at half marathon pace. The key to this workout is to NOT exceed that tempo range. If you feel like you're at 10k RPE, then you're going too hard. Try to dial up the intensity one small increment each time. Imagine you're improving your pace by 5 seconds per mile each effort. Recover with 4-5' easy in between each.

This set simulates a triathlon swim where the pace is always fast at beginning, then it settles after a while and you get into pack, then it can tend to finish strong as people starting thinking about getting out of the water. The kick is to simulate getting on the bike. 400 m easy swim warm-up Main set 300 m alternate 50 free/50 non-free 200 kick with board 100 IM  (all with 20 sec rest at easy/steady intensity) 10 x 50 build on 1 min (get faster throughout each 50m effort, last 5m hard with no breathing) 6 x 450 m (400 swim, 50 m kick with Board). The 400 swim is 100m hard, 250 m moderate, then 50 m hard straight into 50 m kick hard with board. Make sure there are pace changes within the 400’s 200m easy backstroke recovery  1-4-1 "Loco" with pull gear. This is a 800 m set where you do a ladder as follows: 25 m hard, 25 m steady, 50 m hard, 50 m steady, 75 m hard, 75 m steady, 100 m hard, 100 m steady, 75 m hard, 75 m steady, 50 m hard, 50 m steady, 25 m hard, 25 m steady. Make sure there is a pace change between steady and hard and don’t do all at same pace. Warm down 300m easy with 30 secs rest Originally from: http://www.ironman.com/triathlon-news/articles/2013/06/ironman-101-swim-workouts.aspx#ixzz3w9IaaPF4

Title: Drills
WorkoutDescription: WU: 300 easy. Then 'swim golf' = 6 x 50 on 15" rest & count strokes. What combination of time and strokes gives you the lowest ‘score?’ (Ex: 43 strokes + 45” = 88).  MS: Swim a moderate effort using the same stroke count in WU set. 8 x 100 (10”) moderate. 4 x 50 kick (20”) moderate.  CD: 200 easy alternating 50 pull, 50 swim.

Title: Easy
WorkoutDescription: Easy spin for 60' in small chain ring. Do this after a long run or race if one is scheduled.

Six-Mile Run with Tempo Intervals Warm-up 2 miles easy If you usually run your 10K at 8 min/mile pace, your warm-up should be closer to a 9–9:30 pace. Starting slow will allow you to really run well during the tempo phase as well as allowing your muscles to get warmed up so you don’t get injured. Don’t be the person who goes out to “win” the warm-up. Main Set 2 miles of alternating 2 min tempo, 2 min easy recovery During the tempo section, if you train with heart rate, your BPM should be about five beats under your 10K race pace Time yourself each time you do this workout for the two-mile set. Ideally over a few months you should get significantly faster. Cool-down

t keeps that high-end speed and keeps you training at a high heart rate and power Warm-up 3 min easy, small chain ring. 5 min big chain ring, gradually picking up the speed every minute until at about 80% of perceived effort. 5 min at 80–90% effort with the last 30 seconds at 100%. 2 minutes easy pedaling. RELATED: High Intensity For High Performance Main Set 5×6 min efforts with 2-min recoveries. Efforts are as follows: 2 min at 85% 2 min at 100% 1 min at 110% 1 min at 120% Read more at http://triathlon.competitor.com/2015/01/training/one-hour-workout-bike-sprints-failure_111476#B0OCZuKqbycI5tPA.99

Pyramid Brick Workout Warm-up 10 min easy on the bike, increasing effort each minute Main Set: 3-min bike at 90% or more. Run ¼ mile at 5K pace 4-min bike at 90% Run ½ mile at 5K pace 5-min bike at 80–90% Run 1 mile at 5K pace 4-min bike at 90% Run ½ mile at 5K pace 3-min bike at 90% or more Run ¼ mile at 5K pace Cool-down: 5 min easy spin. Cadence should be over 100 RPM. Read more at http://triathlon.competitor.com/2015/07/training/one-hour-workout-quick-pyramid-brick_119916#8v1xp22cq36KRzSQ.99

It's Workout Wednesdays with Andy Potts and Polar: ‪#‎WOD‬- ‪#‎bike‬ ‪#‎WU‬: 30 minutes easy build 15 / 10 / 5 minutes at Iron Man / Ironman 70.3 / ‪#‎olympic‬ distance Pace/Effort ‪#‎MS‬: 8 x (2 minutes at ‪#‎HARD‬ / 10 minutes at ‪#‎IM703‬ Pace/effort / 3 minutes at‪#‎easy‬) 1 x 20 minutes at ‪#‎ironman‬ Pace/Effort ‪#‎CD‬: 15 minutes easy cruise with cadence above 95+rpm's

200 swim/200 pull/200 kick/200 swim 6×50 on 1:10 (descend stroke count 1-6) 3×300 on 6:45 (50 kick/100 swim, repeat) 3 x [50 pull on :60 100 pull on 2:00 150 pull on 3:00] 4×150 3:30 (50 free/50 non-free/50 free) *3500 Total* Read more at http://triathlon.competitor.com/2016/01/training/300s-and-pull-intervals-swim-workout-for-triathletes_74184#MmU6FCP0QljDsdVY.99

This is a great trainer workout but can also be done on the road. If you don’t ride with power, use RPE. You’re riding right around threshold for the efforts. If you have more time, you can extend this workout by adding 1–2 more 5 min efforts. Warm-up 15 min easy Main Set 3×5 min at 95% with 3 min recovery at 55% 10 min easy spinning at 55% after intervals 5×1 at 105% with 1 min recovery at 55%
Choose a strength workout...can be of your own creation, dvd, on-demand, pilates, yoga, etc..
Hills baby! . 15' WU . 2 x (5' @ 4% marathon pace + 2' easy) 2 x (4' @ 4% half marathon pace + 2' easy) . 5' CD

Title: 4x250 Endurance 2500 yd
WorkoutDescription: WU: 200 non-free. 500/400/300/200/100 freestyle at T-pace with 100 backstroke or kickboard recovery between each freestyle set. CD: 400 non-freestyle or kicking mix.

Title: Easy
WorkoutDescription: Ride how you feel. If tired ride in Zones 1-2 (RPE 5-6, 60-70IF) alone. If fresh ride in all zones and may be a group ride. Be smart!
Hill Intervals: 10 minute warm-up followed by 4 x 6mins (2mins at 2%, 2mins at 4%, 2mins at 0%).

Warm-up: 10 min at steady Zone 2 endurance (70–75%) 5 min as 20 sec at Zone 4 threshold (90–95%), 40 sec at Zone 1 recovery (55–65%) Main Set: 20 min as: 17 min at Zone 3 tempo (80–85%), 1 min at Zone 4 threshold (90–95%), 2 min at Zone 2 endurance (70–75%) 15 min as: 11 min at Zone 3 tempo (80–85%), 1:30 at Zone 4 threshold (90–95%), 2:30 at Zone 2 endurance (70–75%) 10 min as: 5 min at Zone 3 tempo (80–85%), 2 min at Zone 4 threshold (90–95%), 3 min at Zone 2 endurance (70–75%) Cool-down: 5 min easy Zone 1 recovery

Sample workout: 2-hour bike ride at an easy pace 12–15-mile run at a pace about 10 seconds per mile faster than race pace “Running harder for less time decreases the overall impact on your body and pays off with aerobic gains as well.”
20 Miler for "marathon simulation" 10 mile aerobic threshold sandwiched in the middle of a 20 mile long run.

Title: 2500yds: 4 x Pace 300s
WorkoutDescription: Normally we close hard but today is different. We want to hold the same pace for 4 x 300s. We are going to find that pace early in the workout and then it's game on! . 4 x 200 (odd free, even pull) :30 . Take the average time of these 3 so we get a base pace: 100 Strong :10 100 Moderate :10 100 Easy 1:00 . After averaging your finishing time using the 3 x 100s above, add 5 seconds to it. That's the average pace you should be holding per 100 for the next set. 4 x 300 @ base pace :30 . 200 EASY CD

Title: 60': High Octane 6x2' AeC Efforts + 1x4' AeC + 10" MAX!
WorkoutDescription: We are going to step it up today and layer in lots of high octane efforts. They are short but copious. Really bring it at the end! I suggest starting the first few at the lower end of your zone . 15' WU gradually building to tempo by 12' . Lower end of zone 1' LT + 1' AeC + 4' easy Middle of zone 1' LT + 1' AeC + 4' easy High end of zone 1' LT + 1' AeC + 4' easy . Lower end of zone 2' AeC + 4' easy Middle of zone 2' AeC + 4' easy High end of zone 2' AeC + 4' easy . I'll take what you can give me hear but whatever duration you select, the last 10" has got to be ALL OUT! I hit 4' AeC + 10" max...can you? Between 2 and 4' AeC (start low) + 10" all out! . CD with remaining time

Title: 60': 2 x (20' High AeT @ 95-105 rpm + 5' easy)
WorkoutDescription: This is a pure aerobic engine building workout that also mixes in neuromuscular development through high cadence. It will deceptively wear you down! . 10' WU @ 90-95 rpm . 2 x (20' High AeT @ 95-105 rpm + 5' easy)

Title: 30': Recovery run with drills
WorkoutDescription: Recovery run with some drills at the end. Easy run warm-up for 15-20'. . Using the last 10', mix in at least 3 (or all of them!) of the drills below for 30" and then run easy for 1' after. Drills are to be done on a soft surface; even grass or packed dirt for example. Concentrate on exaggerated good form in each of the exercises as opposed to speed. Recovery is an easy jog/walk back, not a run.  Drills: 1. High knees 2. Butt kicks 3. Skipping 4. High knee->happy feet (go from high knees to very fast cadence and back to high knees) 5. Strides (These bring it all together. Fast, but smooth running. Keep the effort very short such that you are running notably fast, but you maintain form and good running sensations throughout. These are pickups/bursts in speed)

Title: 2200: Little bit of pull & strength...little bit of fun
WorkoutDescription: Lots of fun sets today. It's not as easy as it looks. Definite strength building day while getting to mix it up a little bit. Remember, OWS = open water stroke...practice sighting every 5-7 strokes. . 400 Choice WU 1:00 . 500 Pull :30 25 Tarzan Stroke (head out of the water entire time + 25 Easy :30 . 400 (50 Choice + 50 Free...really try a different stroke!) :30 25 Elementary Backstroke + 25 Free :30 . 300 Pull (50 OWS + 50 Free) :30 25 Tarzan Stroke (head out of the water entire time + 25 Easy :30 . 200 Pull :30 25 Elementary Backstroke + 25 Free :30 . 100 Build....really attack the last 25! . 100 CD

Title: 40': 20' Tempo
WorkoutDescription: Gradually building 15' WU with a few short (30") pick-ups to get the body warmed up. Then build your pace to tempo (half marathon pace). Give yourself 5' CD. Terrain is your choice. If it's hilly, go by RPE and not pace.

Title: 3000yds: Fast 500 + 5x100 @ pace
WorkoutDescription: 400 WU Choice . 3 x 100 (25 Single Arm + 25 Free, repeat) :15 300 (25 kick/50 swim, repeat)  . 8×25 swim (3 FAST! @ :30, 1 easy @ :45)  . 200 Recovery Pull Easy  . 500 FAST For TIME!! (record time)  100 recovery/easy  . 6×50 pull (2 FAST! @ :45, 1 easy @ :60)  . 5 x 100 (hold 500 avg 100 time) :10 . 200 cool-down

Title: 10K Progression Run
WorkoutDescription: Normally we go by duration but today we're switching it up. Use the first mile as easy, comfortable warm-up. Then start to increase the pace. Your goal is for your last mile to be at least 90 seconds faster than your first mile. This will require you to run very savy...perhaps get 15 seconds faster on each mile? It's up to you to decide but I would prefer to see a nice steady progression in pace. Use the final 0.2 as CD. Good luck!

Title: 10x100 @ T-Pace + 5"
WorkoutDescription: WU: 400 swim then 6x50 on 15" RI.  MS: 10x100 @T-pace +3". 15" RI.  CD: 300 easy.

Title: New Weight Training Program
WorkoutDescription: After 5-10' minute aerobic warm up: 3 Warm up Exercises: 1. 3 way lunges (front, side, rear) 2. Macarena's 3. Squat Rows Main Set: 1. Lat Pull Down 2. Pushups on Ball or feet on ball 3. 1 leg squat (Bulgarian Lunge) 2nd Main Set: 1. Dumbell Press 2. Cable Cross 3. W's 4. Doubles http://www.d3multisport.com/blog/index.php/weight-training-adaptation-phase

Title: Strides and 30' Tempo
WorkoutDescription: 15' WU and include 4x20" strides.. Then 30' tempo run at tempo (Zone 3, no faster). 10' cd. Stretch when done and add in Core work!

Title: Bike LT 5x5'
WorkoutDescription: 10' wu, 10' cd. 5' hard at LT (RPE 8, 90IF), 2' easy (zone 2). Do this 5x.

Title: Recovery
WorkoutDescription: Easy spin for 60' in small chain ring. Do this after a long run or race if one is scheduled.

Title: Long Continuous
WorkoutDescription: WU: 300 swim/100 drill MS: 5x (300 swim at T-pace, 100 drill, so 400 total)  CD: 100 ez

Title: Fast
WorkoutDescription: WU: 6 x 50 done as 25 drill of choice, 25 building speed. MS:  500 at T-pace (50” RI). 5 x 25 fast (20” RI). 400 at T-pace (40” RI). 4 x 25 fast (20”RI). 300 at T-pace (30”RI). 3 x 25 fast (20” RI). 200 at T-pace (20” RI). 2 x 25 fast (20” RI). 100 at T-pace. CD: 200 easy kicks and swims of your choice.
15' warm up, then 2x20' of tempo running at 15" a miler SLOWER than 10k pace. Easy 5' in between efforts. 10' cool down.

Title: Hilly
WorkoutDescription: On a very hilly course in all heart rate zones. Elevate heart rate as run progresses. Good form. Quick cadence.

Title: 2300yds: 4x(4x50s) @ base pace
WorkoutDescription: Swim on the easier side in terms of intensity but I always throw a few challenges in there for you. . Choice can be pull, stroke, drill, kick, even pulling on the lane line! 4 x 250 (200 Free + 50 Choice) :30 . 4 x 50 with only 5-6 breaths total (maybe 2 down, 3 on the way back) :30 Watch your finish time on these...calculate the average...this is your "base" pace for rest of workout . 4 x 50 Free base pace :10 200 Pull Easy :15 . 4 x 50 Free base pace :10 200 Pull Easy :15 . 4 x 50 Pull base pace :05 . 200 CD
Do some active stretching and practice some positive mental images of being in future races. Oh, and rest please. Thanks!

Title: 2500yds: 6x100 Descend + 4x125 timed
WorkoutDescription: Lots of pace work. First section is all about holding a consistent pace and getting faster but with the same amount of rest. The last section is going to hurt. That last 125 is all mental. GO GET IT! . 3 x 200 Choice (:30) 4 x 50 Build :20 100 Easy . 6 x 100 (descend every 2 x 100s. Drop at least 1 second per 100) :15 200 Pull easy! 1:00 . 4 x 125 :20 - Capture your time for the first one. For #2 and #3, go 5 seconds slower than #1. For #4, go 5 seconds faster than #1 200 Pull easy! 1:00 . 100 CD
Ride along the trails in FL
Work with Chris and Ginger in Tampa

Title: 75': 2 x (20' Tempo + 10' easy)
WorkoutDescription: Similar workout as last week but a little longer so we extend the easy sections. Gradually building 15' WU with a few short (30") pick-ups to get the body warmed up. Then build your pace to tempo (half marathon pace) for 20'. Give yourself 10' easy and the repeat the set.. Terrain is your choice. If it's hilly, go by RPE and not pace.

Title: 2600yds: 4x(2x50 drill/swim+200 pull) + 6x50 descend
WorkoutDescription: The mainset has lots of drills so swim smoothly today and focus on your form. Then take your learnings from the drills and apply it to the short efforts at the end of the workout. . Two times through... 200 Free :30 200 Pull :30 100 (25 Kick, 25 Swim, repeat) :20 .. Title: 45': Relaxed Negative Split

Title: 3000yds: 3 x pace set (100,200,300)
WorkoutDescription: Pace work and the key is to be very intelligent with the first 100 of the set. This will teach you to swim smooth and efficient. Go out too fast and your arms will be very angry with you on the 300!  . 2 x 200 Choice :30 . 2 x 50 Build :20 1 x 100 timed...think half ironman pace...this will be your "pace" for the rest of the workout. Swim smart! . Three times through... 100 @ pace :15 200 @ pace :20 300 @ pace :30 200 EASY Pull 1:00

Title: 150': Easy long ride @ 75%
WorkoutDescription: Unstructured ride outside or inside. Minimum duration of 2 hours and max of 3 hours. The idea today is not to crush yourself. Ride 70-75% of your FTP. If indoors, select a fun but not too challenging workout. If outside and with a group, go towards the back. If you're going to climb a lot, try to keep the power in more of a tempo-low LT range.

Title: 60': Easy, unstructured run
WorkoutDescription: Unstructured run on rolling terrain. Think marathon pace or slower. Your goal today is to smile and enjoy yourself. Concentrate on your form and mix up the terrain. Don't be scared to hit a trail or run on something softer. Pace does not matter.

Title: 2000yds: 3 x (100 pace + 200 pace + 100 easy)
WorkoutDescription: Short workout but it should beat you down if you swim it HARD. For your timed 100, which sets the stage, think about that first 100-200m of an Olympic distance race...that's the RPE you're gunning for. If you went to slow, don't worry, you have 3 chances to go faster! . 2 x 200 Choice 2 x 50 build 1 x 100 for time. This is your pace for the rest of the workout! . 100 @ pace - 1 second :20 200 @ pace :30 100 easy 1:00 . 100 @ pace - 2 seconds :20 200 @ pace - 1 second :30 100 easy 1:00 . 100 @ pace - 3 seconds :20 200 @ pace - 2 seconds :30 100 easy 1:00 . 4 x 50 smooth

Title: 40': Shakeout Run - you select 2 miles to work @ half marathon pace
WorkoutDescription: Shakeout run. First mile is warm-up. After that you call the ball. Select 2 miles and build them to whatever pace you feel comfortable. Ideally half marathon pace. Other miles, settle into marathon pace. Enjoy!

Title: 3 x 10' climb + 2 x 5' @ LT

Title: Bike TT 30': Assess Fitness
WorkoutDescription: Power Testing Protocol: Long warm up of at least 20'. Then ride 5x1' at 100 rpms, with 1' recovery. Then you'll ride 5’ hard – 95- 100% effort. Then take an easy 10’ easy spinning before starting the test: Pick a route that you can ride for 30 minutes as hard as you can (Other options are 2x20’ with a 2’ recovery, or a 30' on an indoor bike trainer). If you ride outside, then a flat course or out-back course is best. When you are done ride easy for at least 10'. Record average power, speed & heart rate.

Title: Long, Hilly - Race Simulation
WorkoutDescription: 3:15 hour ride in the hills. Let terrain and strength/endurance dictate pace and effort levels on hills. Practice steady hydration and nutrition throughout, keep stopping to a minimum (bathroom & food refills only). Goal here is to get at least 2000-3500 feet of elevation gain. Power on the flats should be 75-85% of FTP, and on the hills, let the Power climb to 90% of FTP. TSS should be under 200.

Title: Long Hilly

Title: Recovery
WorkoutDescription: Start out at a very easy gearing, over 20' gradually increase the resistance to a medium level. Maintain medium resistance for 20' spinning smoothly. Then gradually work back to the easy gear you started with over the last 20' minutes. Purpose is to loosen legs after long run or ride from day before.

Title: AeT - workout 2 - 1:00

Warmup: 600 WU. 6 X 50 no kick (speed dictated by need to stay afloat), 10 seconds rest between sets Main Set: Each of the following should be done in a time that allows for 10 sec rest (ex.: 100s on 1:40, should come in on 1:30). o5 x 100 on TT pace + 20 sec (approximate) o4 x 100 on 5 sec faster than previous set o3 x 100 on 5 sec faster than previous set o2 x 100 on 5 sec faster than previous set o1 x 100 on 5 sec faster than previous set If the last 1 x 100 comes in with a 10 second rest, next time through this workout should be started 5 seconds faster.  **Note start time and last 100 time in log** Cool Down: 200 backstroke 200 free or breast - your choice 200 easy kick
Run on the beach between swim sets
500 Free 2 x 50 strong 400 Steady Pull 2 x 100 Comfortable 300 steady paddles 2 x 150 moderate 6 x 100 paddles breathing every 5

Title: 3500yds: 800->200 with 100s pace & pull/paddle sets
WorkoutDescription: We are focusing on all systems today. Very few easy parts of the this workout. You will be either working on your fitness (100s), your pacing (long stuff), or your strength (pull & paddles). . Broken 800 as WU (600 Free :30 + 100 smooth...this will be your "pace" for the rest of the workout + 100 Easy) 1:007 X 100 @ pace :15 3 X 200 Paddles @ pace - 1 second :30 5 X 100 @ pace -2 seconds :15 400 Paddles and/or Pull Buoy @ pace - 3 seconds 1:00 3 x 100 Free - 4 seconds :15 200 CD EASY! . Pat yourself on the back after that one!!!
4 Loops along Bay Rd. Last 3 miles FAST!

Title: 2100yds: 10x200
WorkoutDescription: Lots of 200s but they are broken and this will be fun. Once you finish the 5th one, things will move rapidly and you'll be done with the workout quickly! Take 30-45 seconds in between all 200 sets. . 200 Free easy 200 Pull 200 (25 Drill + 25 Free, repeat) 200 Free faster than pull set 200 (4 x 50 build :10 in between each) Repeat! . 100 CD

300 free...cruise  300 fins...try to find my stroke 300 free...little faster 300 paddles...smack a gel after 300 FAST...way faster than race pace . 3 x 100 @ IM pace RPE on 1:30 300 fins... active recovery 3 x 100 @ IM pace RPE on 1:30 3 x 100 faster than IM RPE on 1:30 3 x 50 @ IM RPE on :50 3 x 50 @ faster than IM RPE

Title: 50': 3 x (5' @ half marathon RPE + 5' @ marathon RPE)
WorkoutDescription: Aerobic run that will have you focus on your pacing. Make sure your heart rate comes down during the easier marathon RPE sections. . 15' WU . Run through this 3 timess... 5' @ half marathon RPE 5' @ marathon RPE . 5' CD

Title: 65': 40 high AeT @ varying cadence
WorkoutDescription: Simple workout but it won't be easy. More mentally challenging. Play with your cadence. Start out at a higher cadence for first 20' of the 40' set. Then move to 85-90 rpm for the second half of the workout. . 20' WU...gradually build it . 40' @ High AeT . 5' CD

Title: 1700yds: 3 x(2x100 @ varying RPEs + 1x100 @ RPE 5)
WorkoutDescription: Good race week swim. Should help to give you an indication as to what feels too fast for your race or what feels about right. Remember RPE is on a scale of 1-10. 1 = floating and 10 = all sprint...getting chased by a shark!. . 300 Free :45 300 Paddles :45 . 4 x 50 descend :20 . 2 x 100 @ RPE 8 :30 1 x 100 @ RPE 5 :30 . 2 x 100 @ RPE 7 :30 1 x 100 @ RPE 5 :30 . 2 x 100 @ RPE 5/6 :30 1 x 100 @ RPE 5 as CD

Title: 60': 5x(2' @ race pace + 5' easy)
WorkoutDescription: Easy warm-up then some race efforts. Have the first 2 efforts be slightly under race effort. The last 3 should be dialed in! . 15' WU . 2 x (2' @ perceived race pace + 5' easy) . 10' High AeT . 3 x (2' @ perceived race pace + 5' easy)

Title: 30': 10' @ perceived race pace
WorkoutDescription: Let's see you dial in your pace in the middle of the workout and then shut it down. Find your speed and hold it. Don't over do it...settle into your sweet spot. . 10' WU . 5' gradual build . 10' @ perceived race pace . 5' CD

Title: 1500yds: Pre-Race Swim w 2x100,50,25s
WorkoutDescription: It's all about feeling the water. Remember, OWS = Open Water Stroke..practice sighting . 3 x 200 :45 1. Free 2. Pull 3. 150 Free + 50 OWS . 4 x 75 (25 DPS + 25 FTD + 25 Free) :20 . 2 x 100 @ race pace on :30 2 x 50 @ race pace :20 2 x 25 @ breakout race pace (when you start the race) :15 50 Easy . 200 Pull as CD

Title: 45': 4x(4' building to high AeT + 1' Race pace effort)
WorkoutDescription: For this ride, keep the cadence high (95-100 rpm) throughout the ride. This can be done inside or outside. If outside, ride high AeT with a short effort and then easy, rinse, and repeat :) . 20' WU (higher cadence) . 4 x (4' AeT->High AeT + 1' Race Pace effort) . 5' CD

Title: 20': Openers
WorkoutDescription: Openers...loosen the legs and get them ready to fire! Ride between 90-100 rpm. . 10' WU . 2 x (1' @ perceived race pace + 4' Recovery)

Title: 2100yds: 8x200 + 8x50
WorkoutDescription: Workout that starts off quick and works you on the 200s. Please let me know how you feel during the 50s! It’ll be a good indication on where you stand with your swimming . 200 Free...little quicker than WU pace (Divide time by 2. This is your pace for workout) 200 Free @ pace -2 seconds 200 Free @ pull easy 200 Free @ pace -3 seconds 200 Free @ pace 200 Free @ pace -4 seconds 200 Free @ pace -5 seconds . Your 50s should be challenging at first but by #4 or #6, it will get easier and you’ll feel like you can go faster. The sooner this feeling sets in depends on your fitness. When did you feel comfortable or that you could go faster? 8 x 50 @ pace – 2 seconds :20 . 100 CD
Run on the beach in Cape May

Title: 50': 2 x 20' Aerobic burner
WorkoutDescription: Simple aerobic workout that will make you sweat. Ideal for the trainer but if you go outside, extend the WU and CD to ride for 60-65'. If you don't have power, use RPE scale (1-10, with 10 being MAX!) as follows: Tempo = 7, LT = 8, AeC = 9, AnC = 10. (15' High AeT + 5' low tempo) @ 90-95 rpm 5' easy @ 95 rpm (15' Tempo + 5' low LT) @ 85-90 rpm 5' easy @ 95 rpm' CD

Title: 80' Holiday Ladder
WorkoutDescription: Fun holiday ladder workout that will have you dreaming of climbing and descending a Christmas Tree or Menorah. For the easy sections, go 95+ rpm and EASY! On the way up with the 85-90 rpm, use the middle of your zones. For the 65-75 rpm section, use the upper end of your zones! If you don't have power, use RPE scale (1-10, with 10 being MAX!) as follows: Tempo = 7, LT = 8, AeC = 9, AnC = 10. 10' WU . 5' Tempo @ 85-90 rpm + 5' easy 5' LT @ 85-90 rpm + 5' easy 3' AeC @ 85-90 rpm + 3' easy 1' AnC @ 85-90 rpm + 3' easy 5' AnC @ 65-75 rpm + 5' easy 5' AeC @ 65-75 rpm + 5' easy 5' LT @ 65-75 rpm + 5' easy 5' Tempo @ 65-75 rpm + 5' CD
